Sentencas: The present work explores the application of La0.5Sr0.5Co0.95Nb0.05O3-8 (LSCNO) perovskite as electrode material for the symmetric solid oxide fuel cell.
Titulo: Radio-frequency magnetron sputtered thin-film La0.5Sr0.5Co0.95Nb0.05O3-8 perovskite electrodes for intermediate temperature symmetric solid oxide fuel cell (IT-SSOFC)

Sentencas: Symmetric solid oxide fuel cells of thin-film LSCNO electrodes were prepared to study the oxygen reduction reaction at intermediate temperature.
Titulo: Radio-frequency magnetron sputtered thin-film La0.5Sr0.5Co0.95Nb0.05O3-8 perovskite electrodes for intermediate temperature symmetric solid oxide fuel cell (IT-SSOFC)

Sentencas: The Rietveld refinement of synthesized material shows a hexagonal structure with the R-3c space group of the prepared perovskite material.
Titulo: Radio-frequency magnetron sputtered thin-film La0.5Sr0.5Co0.95Nb0.05O3-8 perovskite electrodes for intermediate temperature symmetric solid oxide fuel cell (IT-SSOFC)

Sentencas: Lattice parameter and fractional coordinates were utilized to calculate the oxygen ion diffusion coefficient for molecular dynamic simulation.
Titulo: Radio-frequency magnetron sputtered thin-film La0.5Sr0.5Co0.95Nb0.05O3-8 perovskite electrodes for intermediate temperature symmetric solid oxide fuel cell (IT-SSOFC)

Sentencas: At 973 K, the oxygen ion diffusion of LSCNO was 1.407 x 10-8 cm2 s-1 higher by order of one magnitude than that of the La0.5Sr0.5CoO3-8 (7.751 x 10-9 cm2 s-1).
Titulo: Radio-frequency magnetron sputtered thin-film La0.5Sr0.5Co0.95Nb0.05O3-8 perovskite electrodes for intermediate temperature symmetric solid oxide fuel cell (IT-SSOFC)

Sentencas: The results suggest that the Nb doping provide the structural stability which improves oxygen anion diffusion.
Titulo: Radio-frequency magnetron sputtered thin-film La0.5Sr0.5Co0.95Nb0.05O3-8 perovskite electrodes for intermediate temperature symmetric solid oxide fuel cell (IT-SSOFC)

Sentencas: The enhanced structural stability was analysed by the thermal expansion coefficient calculated experimentally and from molecular dynamics simulations.
Titulo: Radio-frequency magnetron sputtered thin-film La0.5Sr0.5Co0.95Nb0.05O3-8 perovskite electrodes for intermediate temperature symmetric solid oxide fuel cell (IT-SSOFC)

Sentencas: Furthermore, the density functional theory calculation revealed the role of Nb dopant for oxygen vacancy formation energy at Sr-O and La-O planes is lower than the undoped structure.
Titulo: Radio-frequency magnetron sputtered thin-film La0.5Sr0.5Co0.95Nb0.05O3-8 perovskite electrodes for intermediate temperature symmetric solid oxide fuel cell (IT-SSOFC)

Sentencas: To understand the ratelimiting process for sluggish oxygen diffusion kinetics, 80 nm and 40 nm thin films were fabricated using radio frequency magnetron sputtering on gadolinium doped ceria electrolyte substrate.
Titulo: Radio-frequency magnetron sputtered thin-film La0.5Sr0.5Co0.95Nb0.05O3-8 perovskite electrodes for intermediate temperature symmetric solid oxide fuel cell (IT-SSOFC)

Sentencas: The impedance was observed to increase with an increasing thickness, suggesting the bulk diffusion as a rate-limiting step for oxygen ion diffusion.
Titulo: Radio-frequency magnetron sputtered thin-film La0.5Sr0.5Co0.95Nb0.05O3-8 perovskite electrodes for intermediate temperature symmetric solid oxide fuel cell (IT-SSOFC)

Sentencas: The electrochemical performance was analysed for the thin-film symmetric solid oxide fuel cell, which achieved a peak power density of 390 mW cm-2 at 1.02 V in the presence of H2 fuel on the anode side and air on the cathode side.
Titulo: Radio-frequency magnetron sputtered thin-film La0.5Sr0.5Co0.95Nb0.05O3-8 perovskite electrodes for intermediate temperature symmetric solid oxide fuel cell (IT-SSOFC)
